## 1. Definitions

**"Software"** means the AgentRail source code, object code, documentation,
configuration files, and any other material made available by the
Licensor under this License, together with any modifications,
translations, adaptations, or derivative works of any of the foregoing.

**"Licensor"** means Onyeka Nwamba, the copyright holder of the Software,
and any successor in interest.

**"You"** means the individual or legal entity exercising rights under
this License.

**"Your Organization"** means the legal entity, sole proprietorship, or
other organization for which You act, together with all entities that
control, are controlled by, or are under common control with that
organization. "Control" means ownership of more than fifty percent (50%)
of an entity's voting equity, or the power to direct its management and
policies by contract or otherwise.

**"Internal Use"** means use of the Software by You or Your Organization
for Your Organization's own business operations, including use by
employees, contractors, and agents acting on Your Organization's
behalf, where the Software is not made directly available to Third
Parties as a product, service, or hosted offering.

**"Third Party"** means any individual or legal entity that is not You
or Your Organization.

**"Restricted Offering"** means any act of making the Software, in
original or modified form, available to any Third Party in any of the
following ways: (a) charging a fee, royalty, subscription, license fee,
or other payment for the Software; (b) charging a fee for any product
or service whose primary feature, value, or substantial functionality
is provided by the Software; (c) bundling, embedding, or incorporating
the Software into a paid product or service offered to Third Parties
where the Software provides material value to that product or service;
or (d) operating, hosting, or providing the Software (modified or
unmodified, for fee or free of charge) as a service, platform, or
remote interface that exposes a material set of the Software's features
or functionality to Third Parties.

**"Competing Product"** means a product or service that (i) is offered
to Third Parties, (ii) incorporates or is derived from the source code
of the Software, and (iii) is substantially similar in purpose and
functionality to the Software or to any commercial product the Licensor
offers based on the Software. A product is not a Competing Product
solely because it was built using the Software as a tool, where the
Software's source code is not incorporated into and does not provide
material functionality to that product.

**"Outputs"** means files, code, documents, configurations, designs,
data, or other materials created, generated, edited, or assisted by the
Software in the course of Your or Your Organization's permitted use.

